sentence: Wall Street's major averages were mixed at the close on Tuesday with the Nasdaq pulling ahead on record highs in FANG stocks, but the Dow trading with a small loss from weakness in component stocks Johnson & Johnson ( JNJ ) and Procter & Gamble ( PG ) after reporting mixed Q4 results.

Wall Street's major averages set new record highs in early trade, buoyed by upbeat quarterly results, specifically from Netflix and Travelers, and erasing premarket losses tied to President Donald Trump's imposition of steep tariffs on imported washing machines and solar products.
Investors worried that the action would ignite a deeper trade war with China, Japan and South Korea, and open the door to further tariffs against products from North America and Europe.
Tuesday's only economic data generated little reaction from investors even as the Richmond Fed manufacturing index recorded its largest two-month decline since 2006.
The index fell to 14 in January from 20 in December, missing estimates to pull back to 18.
